# Next.js frontend (AgencyOS product UI)

## Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 15 App Router (`src/app`)
- **UI:** React 19, Tailwind CSS, `clsx` / `tailwind-merge`, Lucide icons
- **Data:** `src/lib/api.ts` — typed async functions; replace bodies with `fetch` to the Express API when integrated
- **Auth (demo):** `src/lib/auth/context.tsx` + `localStorage` — not production-grade

## Conventions

- Prefer **client components** only where needed (`"use client"`); keep server components default when you add RSC-friendly data loading later.
- **Do not** mix Express `project.mdc` conventions (CommonJS, raw SQL) into React files — that rule applies to `src/server.js` and `src/routes`.
- **Types:** Import shared models from `src/types`.
- **Demo integrity:** Coherent copy and demo data (`src/lib/demo-data.ts`); do not imply live revenue/traction without real data sources.

## File placement

- Routes: `src/app/<segment>/page.tsx`
- Shared UI: `src/components/`
- Utilities: `src/lib/utils.ts`, `src/lib/api.ts`

## Environment

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_USE_DEMO_DATA` — controls demo stubs in `api.ts` (see `agencyos-yc-product` skill).
